    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 164, Number 57 (Tuesday, April 10, 2018)]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. FERGUSON:H.R. 5446.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8, The Congress shall have Power to layand collect taxes, duties, imposts and excises, to pay thedebts and provide for the common defense and general welfareof the United States; but all duties, imposts and excusesshall be uniform throughout the United States[Page H3095]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
