    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-04-16T14:51:44Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2018-04-10</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to limit the authority of the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to immediately sell certain seized property to perishable goods. </p> <p>(Under current law, the IRS may sell the property after it has been appraised and the owner has been given the opportunity to pay the appraised value or furnish a bond for payment. The authority currently applies to property that is liable to perish, is liable to become greatly reduced in price, or cannot be kept without great expense.)</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-04-10T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
